<http://www.opengis.net/ont/crs/ConicalCoordinateSystem> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.opengis.net/ont/crs/ConicalCoordinateSystem> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "conical coordinate system" .
<http://www.opengis.net/ont/crs/ConicalCoordinateSystem> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.opengis.net/ont/crs/3DCoordinateSystem> .
<http://www.opengis.net/ont/crs/ConicalCoordinateSystem> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.opengis.net/ont/crs/OrthogonalCoordinateSystem> .
<http://www.opengis.net/ont/crs/ConicalCoordinateSystem> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "An conical coordinate system is a three-dimensional orthogonal coordinate system consisting of concentric spheres (described by their radius r) and by two families of perpendicular cones, aligned along the z- and x-axes, respectively" .
